As part of measures to contain the spread of the dreaded coronavirus, Yobe State government has ordered the closure of all public and private schools in the state for a period of one month. A statement issued by the Commissioner Ministry of Basic and Secondary Education, Dr. Muhammad Sani Idriss indicated that the closure will commence from Thursday, 26th of March 2020 to Sunday, 26th April, 2020. According to the statement, “Following the recent pandemic outbreak of Corona Virus globally and particularly in Nigeria which have endemically affected about 30 people in different states of the federation, His Excellency Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni has directed all institutions in the state both public and private to be closed as from Thursday, 26th of March 2020 to Sunday, 26th April, 2020. “Similarly, His Excellency wishes to extend his appreciation to all parents/guardians for their support and understanding in the state under this trying period and charged them to pray fervently to Allah (SWT) to wipe away this pandemic globally,” the statement added. The statement further indicated that “with this notice all Principals/Head Teachers of both public and private schools under the ministry are hereby informed to take immediate action towards actualising this directive.”